You asked:

“What else is there besides creating, maintaining, living, experiencing, embodying, or destroying?”

Some candidates I’d add are:

* Discovering (finding what already exists)
* Revealing (making the hidden visible)
* Connecting (forming new relationships)
* Separating (differentiating what was conflated)
* Transforming (changing form while preserving something)
* Remembering (preserving through time)
* Forgetting (strategically releasing information)
* Selecting (choosing among possibilities)
* Reconciling (bringing conflicting structures into coherence)
* Playing (exploring without immediate optimization)

Those aren’t necessarily separate from creation or destruction, but they highlight different operators.

